cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.CL

The paper uses machine learning algorithms to predict protests using Twitter data, which falls under the category of social media analysis. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with data mining and predictive modeling, which could fall under cs.SD (Data Mining) and cs.CY (Computational Complexity and Cryptography). The paper also discusses the use of Twitter for political events, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
